{"id": 223773486, "title": "Detection dog must have been exhausted, says judge, as five before court for drug possession", "text": "Cillian O\u2019Brien, aged 20, of Glencorry, Garryspillane, Co Limerick, an architecture student, was caught by a plain-clothes garda in possession of \u20ac100 worth of cocaine. He had no previous convictions. He was given the benefit of the Probation Act and ordered to make a \u20ac400 donation to Unicef. Dane Hurn, aged 29, of Giolla Rua, Shean Upper, Station Rd, Blarney, Co Cork, was caught with a clear plastic bag containing \u20ac140 worth of cocaine. The court heard that the bricklayer had eight previous convictions. Judge Roberts convicted him and sentenced him to 120 hours of community service in lieu of three months in prison. Tom Casey, aged 22, of Highfield Lodge, Glanmire, Co Cork, was arrested for possession of cocaine valued at \u20ac40. The court heard he had no previous convictions. He was given the benefit of the Probation Act and made a \u20ac400 donation to the Society of St Vincent de Paul (SVP). Timmy Ryan, aged 28, of 41 Cluain Duabh, Father Russel Rd, Limerick, was caught in possession of a bag of cocaine valued at \u20ac100. He was ordered to donate \u20ac400 to SVP and given the benefit of the Probation Act. Daniel O\u2019Connell, aged 27, of 63 Meadow Park Rd, Ballyvolane, Cork, was caught in possession of cocaine valued at \u20ac70. His solicitor, Ciaran O\u2019Keeffe, told the court that Mr O\u2019Connell had been through a difficult time and had been homeless. He had no previous convictions. Mr O\u2019Connell was ordered to make a \u20ac300 donation to SVP by September 13. Judge Roberts said that the detection dog at the Indiependence festival must have been exhausted when the weekend was over.", "summary": "All caught with cocaine at music festival last August", "url": "https://www.irishexaminer.com/news/courtandcrime/arid-41403134.html", "image": "https://www.irishexaminer.com/cms_media/module_img/8265/41